Using a variety of hardware types, drivers, and communication channels makes it much harder for a single spyware or hacking tool, like Pegasus, to work everywhere. Such tools often rely on specific device weaknesses or software setups. Mixing devices and connections creates many different “environments,” forcing attackers to develop many unique methods instead of one easy solution. This diversity increases security by reducing the risk of a single exploit compromising all your devices. Keywords to explore include “hardware diversity,” “driver vulnerabilities,” and “multi-channel security.”